"{\"uid\": \"flotrack.org-articles-12766194-when-are-the-1500m-races-at-the-2024-paris-olympic-games-what-to-know\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"TRE LIVE  PSU T&F Winter Classic  GVSU Holiday Open  St. Jude Memphis Marathon  BU Sharon Colyear-Danville Season Opener  Springfield T&F Season Opener  Spartan Alumni Holiday Retreat  River Hawk Early Season Invite  Valencia Marathon  Holiday Kickoff Open  Tiffin Track Meet #1  Brooks XC Championships  The Marathon Project  Phoenix Track & Field Invite  Kaye & JJ Smith Invitational  The 1,500-meter events at the2024 Olympic Gamesin Paris are stacked with talent, history, rivalries and potential, and the excitement is scheduled to unfold over seven days at Stade de France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 327, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\", \"score\": 0.9999999959131856, \"rank\": 4.086714187383267e-09, \"text\": \"Phoenix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Raceway\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5970842504768713e-54, \"text\": \"Track & Field\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Track_and_field\"}, {\"begin\": 437, \"end\": 442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.782916866864965e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 563, \"end\": 578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The starting fields this week in Paris include both champions from the 2020 games in Tokyo -Jakob Ingebrigtsenof Norway andFaith Kipyegonof Kenya.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.782916866864965e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999167282401874, \"rank\": 8.327690438309509e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999951901373, \"rank\": 4.226791733669635e-09, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are also the Olympic record holders in the event with 3:28.32 and 3:53.11, respectively, both accomplished in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999167282401874, \"rank\": 8.327690438309509e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The preliminary round of the men's 1,500m was completed Friday, the 24-athlete field for the semifinals was set following the repechage round Saturday and the list was narrowed again with two semifinal heats Sunday.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final of the men's 1,500 at Stade de France is scheduled for Tuesday at 2:50 p.m. Eastern.\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1100, \"end\": 1115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women also will hit the track Tuesday for their 1,500-meter race, with the first round helping kick off the day's track and field action in Paris.\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1308, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.782916866864965e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For those who do not advance automatically, the women's repechage round Wednesday at 6:45 a.m. EDT will give them a second chance.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The semifinals will be held Thursday at 1:35 p.m. EDT, and the medals finally will be on the line Saturday at 2:25 p.m. EDT.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's 1,500 these days, two names immediately come to mind - Ingebrigtsen and Josh Kerr of Great Britain.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Duggar\", \"score\": 0.6859952227217642, \"rank\": 0.45725300046269407, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Duggar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Duggar\"}, {\"begin\": 1671, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997439172476, \"rank\": 2.5604808611855244e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The former is the defending champion at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter is the reigning world champion.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1782, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ingebrigtsen has beaten Kerr in eight of the nine times they have lined up for the finals of a 1,500-meter race, but Kerr has proven the potential is there.\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also made the podium in Tokyo, taking the bronze medal, so his 2024 effort could be fueled by a combination of confidence, experience and possible redemption.\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999167282401874, \"rank\": 8.327690438309509e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Between them on the podium in the last Olympics was Timothy Cheruiyot of Kenya, a past world champion who's always a threat, too.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Timothy_Cheruiyot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Timothy Cheruiyot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Timothy_Cheruiyot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Timothy_Cheruiyot\"}, {\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999951901373, \"rank\": 4.226791733669635e-09, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In this year's Olympic semifinals, Ingebrigtsen and Kerr ran in the same semifinal, finishing first and second, and Cheruiyot was in the other.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one male athlete in history, Great Britain's Sebastian Coe, has won the Olympic 1,500 twice - 1980 and 1984.\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2493, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2414, \"end\": 2427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997439172476, \"rank\": 2.5604808611855244e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2430, \"end\": 2443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beyond Ingebrigtsen's Olympic record in Japan, the world record belongs to Hicham El Guerrouj of Morocco - a 3:26.00 performance in 1998.\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.92658049249694, \"rank\": 0.07923609600981184, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2570, \"end\": 2588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hicham_El_Guerrouj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hicham El Guerrouj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hicham_El_Guerrouj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hicham_El_Guerrouj\"}, {\"begin\": 2592, \"end\": 2599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.969566534896653, \"rank\": 0.03138873298169806, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ingebrigtsen does now own the No.\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"6 time in history, a 3:26.73 effort at this year's Diamond League Monaco meet in July.\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2718, \"end\": 2732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999735910027, \"rank\": 2.640920881487832e-08, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 2733, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"score\": 0.9999999507335827, \"rank\": 4.7804550079419264e-08, \"text\": \"Monaco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"See who qualified for the finals of the men's 1,500 in the City of Light:  Six athletes from each of the Men's 1500m Semi-Finals advanced to Tuesday's#Paris2024Finals!All three \\ud83c\\uddfa\\ud83c\\uddf8 move on to the final \\ud83d\\ude24Heat 1\\ud83c\\uddf3\\ud83c\\uddf4 Jakob Ingebrigtsen - 3:32.38\\ud83c\\uddec\\ud83c\\udde7 Josh Kerr - 3:32.46\\ud83c\\uddfa\\ud83c\\uddf8 Cole Hocker - 3:32.54\\ud83c\\uddf0\\ud83c\\uddea Brian Komen - 3:32.57\\ud83c\\uddf3\\ud83c\\uddf1 Stefan Nillessen - 3:32.73\\ud83c\\uddee\\ud83c\\uddf9\\u2026  The new-to-the-Olympics repechage round gives all athletes the chance to run two races at the Olympics, compared to possibly just one in the past.\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 3244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It also could serve as a second chance for someone who may have suffered some kind of mishap.\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The concept has been introduced for all individual track events from the 200 meters to the 1,500, including the hurdles.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first event to feature the change was the women's 800 meters on Saturday.\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:What Is A Repechage Round At The 2024 Olympics?\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's What To Know  Just like the men's 1,500, there is plenty of name recognition in the women's field for this year's Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3734, \"end\": 3747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999342213648593, \"rank\": 5.909801162623349e-05, \"text\": \"Olympic Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Leading the way is Kenya's Kipyegon, the two-time defending Olympic champion, reigning world champ and the owner of both the world (3:49.04) and Olympic (3:53.11) records in the event.\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3778, \"end\": 3783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999951901373, \"rank\": 4.226791733669635e-09, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, Kipyegon became the third athlete in history to successfully defend the Olympic title, and the three also are the only competitors to win more than one 1,500m gold medal at the Olympics - Tatyana Kazankina (1976, 1980), Sebastian Coe (1980, 1984) and Kipyegon (2016, 2020).\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 4231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3952, \"end\": 3971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998613021, \"rank\": 1.3881673736974915e-10, \"text\": \"2020 Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4161, \"end\": 4178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatyana_Kazankina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tatyana Kazankina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatyana_Kazankina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tatyana_Kazankina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among those looking to challenge Kipyegon in Paris, three can be found on the list of the 15 fastest 1,500 times in history - Gudaf Tsegay of Ethiopia, Jessica Hull of Australia and Sifan Hassan of the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 4233, \"to\": 4447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4374, \"end\": 4386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gudaf Tsegay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\"}, {\"begin\": 4374, \"end\": 4386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gudaf Tsegay\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gudaf_Tsegay\"}, {\"begin\": 4390, \"end\": 4398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9404823525728552, \"rank\": 0.06328417248369747, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 4400, \"end\": 4412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Hull\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Hull\"}, {\"begin\": 4416, \"end\": 4425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9495367526884926, \"rank\": 0.04141100530380233, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4430, \"end\": 4442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sifan Hassan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sifan_Hassan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hassan is the defending Olympic champion in the 5,000- and 10,000-meter races.\", \"from\": 4448, \"to\": 4526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4450, \"end\": 4461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9536898357823813, \"rank\": 0.033797076406757144, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Times Eastern  Aug. 2  Aug. 3  Aug. 4  Aug. 6  Aug. 6  Aug. 7  Aug. 8  Aug. 10  The Olympics are on the NBC family of networks, including the Peacock streaming app.\", \"from\": 4528, \"to\": 4696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"FloTrack is on the ground in Paris with the latest news.\", \"from\": 4698, \"to\": 4754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get the latest news and notes and vibes from Paris on FloTrack.\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4804, \"end\": 4809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vibraphone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"vibes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vibraphone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vibraphone\"}, {\"begin\": 4815, \"end\": 4820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.782916866864965e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss all the track and field season action streaming on FloTrack.Check out the FloTrack schedule for more events.\", \"from\": 4820, \"to\": 4940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video footage from each event will be archived and stored in a video library for FloTrack subscribers to watch for the duration of their subscriptions.\", \"from\": 4942, \"to\": 5093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5026, \"end\": 5033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Library\", \"score\": 0.9999999108331434, \"rank\": 8.80418652305868e-08, \"text\": \"library\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Library\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Library\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  Get the most important Track & Field stories delivered straight to your inbox.\", \"from\": 5095, \"to\": 5180, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92006 - Present FloSports, Inc. All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 5182, \"to\": 5234, \"entities\": []}]}"